<main class="container">
<h1>The Persona Series: Identity and the Social Self</h1>


<section class="grid">
<article class="card">
<h2>Masks &amp; Selves</h2>
<p><strong>Core idea:</strong> We wear masks to navigate society. The series literalizes this with Personae—facets of the psyche we summon. Titles like <cite>Persona 3</cite>, <cite>Persona 4</cite>, and <cite>Persona 5</cite> reimagine selfhood as a system you actively shape.</p>
</article>


<article class="card">
<h2>Jungian Roots</h2>
<p>Key terms—<ruby lang="ja">シャドウ<rt>shadow</rt></ruby>, <ruby lang="ja">アルカナ<rt>arcana</rt></ruby>—connect mechanics to archetypes. Confronting a Shadow dramatizes integration: accepting disowned traits to become whole.</p>
</article>


<article class="card">
<h2>Ethics of Community</h2>
<p>Social Links/Confidants turn relationships into a practice of virtue: trust, reciprocity, and responsibility. Progress isn’t just stats—it’s learning how to be with others.</p>
</article>


<article class="card">
<h2>Everyday Life as Philosophy</h2>
<p>Time management raises questions of the good life: what deserves your limited days? Play itself becomes an ethics of attention.</p>
</article>
</section>


